# sqlite as a guest — vendor LESS, patch in place (VISION §8, B3). Upstream source
# enters via http_archive(urls, sha256, patches=[...]) in MODULE.bazel; ONLY our deltas
# live in-tree:
#   patches/             — the `// mc PATCH` set as real .patch files (B3).
#   glue/                — wasi_compat etc., written in ZIG, compiled by `zig cc`.
#   BUILD.sqlite.bazel   — the build_file http_archive applies to the extracted source.
#
# The build stamps mc_tier / mc_budget / mc_service so /bin/sqlite is both a one-shot
# CLI and a resident service from ONE binary (§4.5).
#
